cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on secure multi-party computation and proof-carrying code to provide privacy and correctness guarantees for smart contracts on blockchains.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper deals with smart contracts on blockchains, which are inherently distributed systems.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper may involve the use of data structures and algorithms for secure multi-party computation and proof-carrying code.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper deals with smart contracts, which are written in programming languages.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the practical viability of the implementation of Raziel for private and verifiable crowdfundings and investment funds.
